 As a former member of the European Parliament (1999–2004), he is also a public intellectual. This book takes up his call to advance the crucial active and affirmative engagement with thinking and society. More than just interpretations of Vattimo's thinking, these essays are expressions of the new impetus given to hermeneutic philosophy by "weak thought," the term he coined for how we think now in the wake of Nietzsche, Heidegger, and Gadamer. The development of Vattimo's thinking is reflected in the organization of the volume, divided into three main parts: Hermeneutics and Nihilism, Metaphysics and Religion, and Politics and Technology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 4aPhilosophy : Hermeneutics. 4aPhilosophy : Phenomenology. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Theory. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Phenomenology.2bisacsh1 aAguirre, Edison Higuera, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBagetto, Luca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBenso, Silvia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBenso, Silvia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBorradori, Giovanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarravetta, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChiurazzi, Gaetano, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCiancio, Claudio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aD’Agostini, Franca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMendieta, Eduardo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRisser, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 